messages.content: "Why are you here?" The duchess.
‚ÄúTo speak with your prisoner.‚Äù

"*My* prisoner?" She chuckles mockingly. "I believe he prefers the term son."

Theo looks confused.

"I suppose these roles are not so different." Aliza speaks wisely, prompting a look of annoyance on the Duchess's face.
‚ÄúWhat.‚Äù

"I suppose you wouldn't understand the trappings of family, Aeolian." Aliza.

"Call it a joke. I have nothing to do with the prisoner here. I was here for my son." The Duchess.
‚ÄúOkay. Great joke.‚Äù
"Hm." The Duchess smirks. "You're not very good at this, are you?" She heads off.
‚ÄúAwkward.‚Äù I enter the building.

They are directed to a large room containing a cell in the center. This room would normally be used for ritual purposes to punish criminals in the name of libra. Locruz is locked inside. Nash Edwardson is guarding him along with 2 other guards.
‚ÄúMm.‚Äù I acknowledge the existence of someone I have seen in my life before.
"Who are you?" Male guard with Nash.
Nash looks at Burr with disdain.
‚ÄúI‚Äôm Aeolian Burr.‚Äù
Nash waves a hand dismissively. "Yes, yes. What are you *doing* here, is the prudent question."
‚ÄúI came to speak with my acquaintance, who was arrested in an illegal act of terrorism that collapsed a building on those inside. I‚Äôm highly curious what led to such a thing.‚Äù
Nash laughs unkindly. "Why do terrorists do anything? To threaten the structure of society. Those are his motives squared away."
‚ÄúThe act of terrorism was not his. I have no idea of anything at all he has done. Such is part of the question.‚Äù
"What? Then who did it?" Female guard.
I roll my eyes. ‚ÄúThe one who arrested him. The ends justify the means, clearly.‚Äù
Nash tilts his head, confused. "Can you stop saying stupid shit?"
‚ÄúNot in any sense.‚Äù
"Ally, you sound like you can only say stupid shit." The woman with Aeolian.
That is a terrible nickname.
"So what do you propose, then?" Nash drawls. "A complete jailbreak? A miscarriage of justice?"
‚ÄúAttempting a jailbreak here would be absurdly foolish, and justice has already been aborted. I, again, merely intend to speak with him.‚Äù I ignore my friend.
"For what purpose?"

I stare blankly at this man asking what I have spent the past several minutes explaining. 

‚Äú‚Ä¶To solve the mystery.‚Äù
"The mystery is solved."
"He's a terrorist."
‚ÄúNo.‚Äù
"Yes."
‚ÄúThat is not a solution.‚Äù
"How is it not."
‚ÄúIt does not have any backing or answer anything.‚Äù
"It does."
‚ÄúHow.‚Äù
"He's a terrorist."
‚ÄúWhat is the backing for that or answers it provides.‚Äù
"He's in jail."
‚ÄúNot an answer to either.‚Äù

"To be clear, I run a street gang. That‚Äôs not terrorism." Locruz.

The female guard hits the bars, silencing him implicitly.
Nash crosses his arms, leaning against the wall behind him. "Still a crime." Probably.
‚ÄúGlad to hear something from you, at least‚Ä¶‚Äù I sigh. ‚ÄúThis is almost wholly unrelated to the purported reason he was taken in.‚Äù

A flash of annoyance crosses Nash‚Äôs face. ‚ÄúWhy does this matter to you‚Ä¶? He‚Äôs a threat to the crown. The specific *crime* might be debatable, I‚Äôll acknowledge that, but he‚Äôs still in jail for a reason.‚Äù
‚ÄúBecause I care about truth, and reason, and the reasons for things.‚Äù
‚ÄúUghhhh.‚Äù Nash says, face contorting. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know why you‚Äôre pretending it makes you a noble truth seeker or whatever to endlessly squabble over technicalities.‚Äù
‚ÄúThey are not mere technicalities. And no, I am not a noble truth-seeker for this reason. This is hardly worth my time.‚Äù
‚ÄúOkay, then leave?‚Äù
‚ÄúNo.‚Äù
‚ÄúYes.‚Äù
‚ÄúNot your decision to make.‚Äù
Nash turns to his boss. ‚ÄúRuth, make him leave.‚Äù
"‚Ä¶We don‚Äôt have that authority, Nash." The female guard who is named Ruth sighs and crosses her arms. "If we let him talk to the prisoner we might learn more too."
‚ÄúUgh‚Ä¶‚Äù Nash mutters. ‚ÄúAnd what if he tries something?‚Äù *Idiot. Obviously he wouldn‚Äôt. And you‚Äôre here to prevent that, so you‚Äôd just have to do your job. Moron.*
"Then we‚Äôll have grounds to stop him." Ruth.
‚Äú‚Ä¶‚Äù
‚ÄúIndeed.‚Äù
"...Whatever."
"Do what you want."
‚ÄúMm. Are you alright, Locruz? Relatively speaking.‚Äù
"No." He sighs. "I'll say this much, though. We didn't have anything to do with that whole assassination attempt. Like, us hellhounds as a whole."
*Yeah, right.* Nash thinks.
‚ÄúUs‚Ä¶ hm. Is the organizational structure not such that such a thing could happen without your knowledge?‚Äù

"It *could* happen without me hearing. But it just wouldn't. I wasn't even hanging around hellhound guys when I got arrested. But it'd be even less possible for those guys to do it. It's all nonsense!"
‚ÄúInteresting. But you don‚Äôt deny an affiliation with them. Do you know what exactly the priestess was suspecting, then?‚Äù
"Not really. She didn‚Äôt listen to anything I was saying! She, uh‚Ä¶ Well I shouldn‚Äôt really be talking about this‚Ä¶ She‚Äôs kind of got her biases about us."
Nash listens to this conversation with trepidation.
‚ÄúI can imagine. What were you doing at that time? At‚Ä¶ the Major‚Äôs, right?‚Äù

"Uh‚Ä¶ Well, at around the same time the emperor was stabbed, some monster killed a bunch of my guys! The major was a witness. I dunno what happened with that though, since he decided to test us for the info and he threw me out of his window."
‚ÄúA monster‚Ä¶?‚Äù
"Yeah. That‚Äôs what I said."
‚ÄúYyess. What sort?‚Äù
"I didn‚Äôt see it."
‚ÄúOh.‚Äù
"Yeah."
‚ÄúWho did? ‚Ä¶the major, I guess‚Ä¶‚Äù
"‚Ä¶Yeah."
‚ÄúRight.‚Äù I nod. ‚ÄúI guess for the reasoning behind your arrest, I‚Äôd have to speak to‚Ä¶‚Äù I hold my head. ‚ÄúAaaagh‚Ä¶‚Äù
"Umm... But is this really relevant to anything, boss?" Aeolian's male follower.
‚ÄúYes‚Ä¶? Well, it may be a red herring‚Ä¶‚Äù
(( @Don'tAtmey @Don'tAtmey @Don'tAtmey ))
"A red herring?"
‚ÄúPerhaps the belief that he has anything to do with the king‚Äôs assassination attempt is merely delusion, conjured based on nothing at all.‚Äù
"I meant the monster."
‚ÄúYess.‚Äù
"Huh?"
‚ÄúYes, that matter may not be related.‚Äù
"I‚Äôd still like to learn more." The woman who called Aeolian Ally.
‚ÄúWell, alright. It is a curious event, certainly. Where did this occur?‚Äù
Locruz gives the address.
‚ÄúCurious indeed‚Ä¶ don‚Äôt let me interrupt you, obviously, if you have any questions, Aliza‚Ä¶‚Äù
"Well, I‚Äôd rather see this fit myself." Aliza just walks out.
‚Äú???????‚Äù I look around. ‚ÄúWell. Sorry about this. I‚Äôll see to getting you a more proper legal defense, hopefully‚Ä¶‚Äù
"We‚Äôve got it handled." Ruth.
‚ÄúWho are you.‚Äù
"Captain Ruth Wayne. We work for the imperial guard."
‚ÄúMmyeh.‚Äù I shrug, and looking over at Locruz and then Nash, who I don‚Äôt know is named that, follow after Aliza.
Ruth steps out of earshot from Locruz. "What did you 2 think of his story?"
Nash sticks out his tongue like a petulant child.
"Huh?‚Äù Orion.

Nash just crosses his arms, staring at the ground. He feels.. taken off-guard. Abandoned. *Not a normal emotion to have. Or response, in any way.* "He's obviously just.. making things up to escape guilt, isn't he?" *Don't look for someone to affirm your responses!*
"Partly. But I do believe him about the monster. I think it‚Äôs the same one we met last night." Ruth.

"Perhaps." Nash says, worrying his bottom lip. *Urgh. Unwilling to concede anything, as usual. You just haaave to let eeeeeveryone know that. It's so obvious you've been outwitted, in some concrete way that's visible to everyone else, and now the country is in danger, and you can't do anything about it! Your world will be.. plundered, violated, and you cannot protect her! How cruel, how cruel...*
"That means Baron Burr might get too close to that monster." Ruth smirks. "That wouldn‚Äôt be too great a loss."
"That's true." Nash says, calming himself. "What a pathetic man."
"Do you know him?" Orion.
"Not personally." Nash scoffs. "But he showed up a while back harassing my family in pursuit of information. Vile."
"We‚Äôll solve this case far earlier than he will." Ruth.
"Yes.." Nash says. "Yes, that's right. So there's nothing to worry about."
*Won't you tell me there's nothing to worry about?*
"There‚Äôs nothing to worry about." Orion nods.
*Ggh... Okay, I guess it can come from you. I guess.*
"Don‚Äôt be stupid." She slaps them both on the side of the head. "You should never stop worrying that easily."
"Ouch, ouch ouch ouch..." Nash whines, covering his head.
"Don‚Äôt be a baby."
Nash just makes a mumbling discontented noise.
((End session sorry))
((that‚Äôs fine))
(( @Don'tAtmey atmeyyyyy))
((I‚Äôm waiting.))
((For me???))
((bash nutton..))
A woman(?) whom Nash would not recognize at all but whom is undoubtedly the one known as "Selle" approaches.
They‚Äôre back outside of the temple.
‚ÄúRight then.‚Äù

"We‚Äôre going to the crime scene then?" Theo.

"Indeed. Away we go!" Aliza heads in the direction mentioned.
I also do this. ‚ÄúWhat an unusual diversion.‚Äù
"It‚Äôs a big week, it seems." Aliza.
‚ÄúNothing ever happens. Until it does.‚Äù
‚ÄúHuh?"
‚ÄúHistorically.‚Äù

"That‚Äôs true." Aliza.

"???" Theo.
‚ÄúNothing begets everything. Think of it this way, Theo. How would you feel if you had not had breakfast this morning?‚Äù
"Huh? Umm‚Ä¶ Hungry?" Theo.
‚ÄúExactly. Good work.‚Äù

"I don‚Äôt get it." Theo.

"Someday you‚Äôll reach our level, perhaps." Aliza.

‚ÄúSuch ignorance is a natural part of the process.‚Äù I am actually myself starting to wonder what I am even saying. Perhaps I can scale it back a bit. ‚ÄúIs there any particular reason you believe investigation of this ‚Äòmonster‚Äô may be fruitful?‚Äù
"Curiosity. I‚Äôve never heard of a monster leaving the catacombs." Aliza.
‚ÄúMmhm.‚Äù I of course know about the catacombs. What are the catacombs.
Right of course. ‚ÄúRight, of course. Perhaps they were inadequately guarded with resources diverted for the event‚Ä¶?‚Äù

They arrive at the district of the address. 

"Not often I see your kind come down to my territory, Baron!" Donald Jameson from the party calls out to him.
‚ÄúDonald Jameson.‚Äù Donald Jameson. I nod.

"The one and only! What‚Äôs a guy like you doing down here?" Donald.

"Is this man important?" Aliza.

"You don‚Äôt know me? Ah! I‚Äôm hurt, truly!" Donald.
‚ÄúYou mentioned Donald Jameson yesterday, I think.‚Äù I mutter.

Aliza pauses, thinking. "Oh, right‚Ä¶ The hellhound leader my father mentioned?"

"Think of me more as a philanthropist with some necessary connections." Donald shrugs. "Your father, though‚Ä¶" He stares at Aliza. "Would that happen to be old man Hamill?"
‚ÄúWell, I was sort of under the impression we shouldn‚Äôt betraying knowing that about him, but alright.‚Äù I shrug.

"You know my father?" Aliza.

"Aha! That figures. Isn‚Äôt he an annoying little bugger?" Donald.

"‚Ä¶Uh, perhaps?" Aliza.
‚ÄúHe said it, not me.‚Äù I chuckle wryly.

"You get me!" Donald gives Aeolian a finger bow and arrow, which is visually identical to the real life finger gun. "What's he up to these days?"

"She isn't going to leak information to a criminal." Theo.

"Tch, you're no fun..." Donald sighs.
‚ÄúIt‚Äôs not relevant, at any rate.‚Äù

Donald sighs overdramatically.

A large crashing sound is audible from the direction of Aeolian's barony. A roar sounds out.

"Shit... Is that thing back above ground!?!?" Donald. 

((End session))
Selle is in the bath.

Selle washes their hair and body, and makes sure to take the time to rest and think about what had just transpired while in there.

*Nothing ever goes smoothly, huh. I suppose it's only right to go and rescue him, regardless of whether my life is on the line.... Also, that "Queen" is seriously a pain in the ass. She definitely asked me all of that for a reason, and also definitely knew all of it before hand too. That means she has some sort of insane information network going on. I'll have to put a lot more effort into this next disguise.*

Selle looks down at their right arm, and sighs. Then, they leave the bath and dry up, as well as applying a bandage around their right arm so it's condition is hidden from view. They then get dressed, and apply their brown contacts the same way as they had when they first entered the inn.

*I'll have to go buy more clothes and sign out of the inn before I actually apply the disguise, so that I don't attract attention. I can scout out a more secluded place for that later.... I should eat something as well. It's been a full day since I've eaten.*

Selle leaves their room, into the main area of the inn, where food is served.
The food came with the price of the room, so Selle receives a meal.

Selle eats the food, and enjoys it, it being their only meal for the past... not even sure how long, days...

Time has really been blending together for me, huh.

They finish up with their meal, go back to collect their things from their room (not much) and give the key back in. They say their thanks and leave to go looking for a clothing store.
A clothing store is relatively easy to find.

Selle enters and looks for items of clothing reminiscent of what their mother would make them wear in their childhood. However, Selle also checks to make sure it's easy to move in said clothes. In the end, they pick out multiple articles of clothing with a similar theming, including a blouse with long sleeves and a longer length skirt that had lots of room to crouch and move around in. As for the rest, They decided their other articles of clothing they already had can be modified to match the theme of the disguise. 

*I'm hoping I have enough money for all this.*
It costs 1sp.

*I think I have plenty of money for anything I need to buy around here.*

Selle buys the things they need, and leaves to go find an area to change.
They can find somewhere to change, sure.
